    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-07-05T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-07-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="108"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d108">
                <head>108. Memorandum by the Secretary of State<note n="1" type="source"
                        xml:id="d108fn1">Source: Department of State, <gloss target="#t_RA1"
                            >RA</gloss> Files: Lot 58 D 374, Atomic Energy Integration.
                        Secret.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-07-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 5, 1955</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>I read Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>’s memorandum on US
                    Policy towards proposed European Atomic Pool.<note n="2" xml:id="d108fn2">
                        <ref target="#d105">Document 105</ref>.</note> I have also read Mr.
                        <persName corresp="#p_SGC1">Smith</persName>’s dissent from Mr. <persName
                        corresp="#p_MLT1">Merchant</persName>’s recommendations.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d108fn3">
                        <ref target="#d106">Document 106</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>I agree with recommendations (1) and (2). I agree with (3a), with emphasis on
                    “assist Belgium”. I do not think we should pressure Belgium.</p>
                <p>With reference to (3b), I do not think we should use delay as a means of
                    coercion. I do not think we should rush these other bilateral arrangements but
                    should go ahead in an orderly way with the understanding that if the pool is
                    agreed upon, we should treat them in the same way as we treat the Belgian
                    agreement.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">
                            <hi rend="strong">JFD</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
